The '''1967 [[Syracuse Orange football|Syracuse Orangemen]] team''' represented [[Syracuse University]] in the 1967 NCAA University Division (the predecessor to today's Division I FBS and FCS) college football season.
==Regular season== In 1967, Tom Coughlin set the school's single-season pass receiving record. Larry Csonka was in his senior season and was named an [[All-American]]. He broke many of the school's [[rush (football)|rushing]] records, including some previously held by [[Ernie Davis]], [[Jim Nance]], [[Floyd Little]], and [[Jim Brown]].
In his three seasons at Syracuse, Csonka rushed for a school record 2,934 yards, rushed for 100 yards in 14 different games, and averaged 4.9 yards per carry. From 1965 to 1967, he ranked 19th, 9th and 5th in the nation in rushing. He was the Most Valuable Player in the EastâWest Shrine Game, the Hula Bowl, and the College All-Star Game.
